==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[άνθρωπος]]''' (''anthropos'') "[[human]]" from two words [[anth]]( flower)which represents woman  and [[rop]]( bush) which represents man + '''[[λόγος]]''' "[[logos]]"= word, study.

===Noun===
'''anthropology'''

# the [[holistic]] scientific and social study of [[humanity]]

====Derived terms====
* [[anthropologic]], or [[anthropological]]
* [[anthropologist]]
* [[cultural anthropology]]
* [[paleoanthropology]]

